---
description: File and code naming conventions for TypeScript and React files. Apply when creating or renaming files, components, hooks, services, or utilities. Enforces kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components, and specific suffix patterns per type.
alwaysApply: true
---

## File & Folder Naming

- Always use **kebab-case** for file and folder names

```
✅ use-playlist-mutation.ts
✅ playlist-embed.tsx
✅ artist-card.skeleton.tsx

❌ usePlaylistMutation.ts
❌ PlaylistEmbed.tsx
```

## Code Naming

| Type            | Convention            | Example          |
| --------------- | --------------------- | ---------------- |
| React component | PascalCase            | `ArtistCard`     |
| Hook            | `use` + camelCase     | `useAudioPlayer` |
| Service         | camelCase + `Service` | `spotifyService` |
| Utility         | descriptive camelCase | `formatDuration` |

## File Suffix Conventions

| Pattern           | Usage                        |
| ----------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `*.container.tsx` | Container (smart) components |
| `use-*.ts`        | Custom hooks                 |
| `*-service.ts`    | Service modules              |
| `*.spec.ts(x)`    | Unit/integration tests       |
| `*.skeleton.tsx`  | Loading skeleton variants    |
